HOWEVER, because of the very limited size of the cartridge, it is plagued with limited power and therefore most of the existing ammo in 32 ACP suffers from not being reliable as a man-stopper. We've studied and examined nearly all available 32 ammo and find it wanting as a reliable means of self defense, especially against a large, drugged up/pain free, determined attacker.Here's the problem. The current 32 ACP frangible ammo delivers a large amount of surface trauma, but lacks sufficient penetration. For example, if you shot me or another sane man in the face, with modern, frangible 32 ACP ammo, it would blow off a big portion of my cheek. I would undoubtedly fall to the ground in shock and pain, but I would be very much alive and functional if I could get past the pain, as that frangible bullet would have stopped somewhere in my face, never making it to my brain. However, if you shot a drugged up maniac in the face with that same frangible bullet and blew half his cheek off, he would keep right on coming because he is insane and is not thinking like you or I. Plus, he is likely pain free and fear free and won't know that part of his cheek is missing and if he did know, he would not care. So, whatever 32 ACP ammo you shoot him in the face with, had better go through his face and blow his brain stem out the back of his head, because only a CNS (central nervous system) hit with a 32 ACP is going to stop him. Likewise, a torso hit to the sternum needs to penetrate deep enough to blow all the way through his spine in order to shut him down instantly. If you fail to shut him down instantly, you and your loved ones are going to have to find a way to survive while you wait for him to bleed out and pass out. The best chance of survival for you and your loved ones, is to shut down the attacker instantly. So, we've designed this 32 ACP+P load to keep you and yours alive under the worst of scenarios.This 32 ACP+P ammo will better all American made 32 ACP+P ammo by 110 fps to 150 fps with a heavier bullet than any other American made 32 ACP ammo.Item 30A/20 is a 75gr. HARD cast bullet with a flat nose. It is traveling over 1,000 fps out of my 3.4 inch Beretta Mod. 70. We've used a flash suppressed powder so that you won't be blinded by your own gunfire in the dark. This is significant as well over 90% of all civilian shootings in America occur in low light when the criminal element is out and about. Also, this flat nosed, nonexpanding, hard cast, bullet will penetrate deeply and will do much more damage than the typical round nosed FMJ bullet. Round nosed bullets tend to slip and slide through living tissue, doing little damage as opposed to a flat nosed bullet. The flat nose not only wounds much more than a round nosed bullet, but it actually keeps the penetration straight and thus deeper. Notice the below velocities from my personal 32 ACP pistols. These are real world guns and thus the speeds are realistic and not the exaggerated speeds you'll see produced from laboratory test barrels. What you see with Buffalo Bore Ammo advertising, is truly what you get in the "real world" where it matters. You can expect 20+ inches of straight line penetration in flesh and bone with this load. If you are worried about over-penetration with this load, DON'T! You chose to carry a tiny under-powered 32 ACP pistol and the trade off is that now you are going to have to stay alive using this pistol and over-penetration will be the least of your worries if you end up needing this gun to save yourself or your family.A. Berretta Mod. 70, 3 inch bbl.- 1001 fpsB. Kel Tek, 2.5 inch bbl - 910 fpsC. Seecamp, 2 inch bbl. - 856 fpsThe above bullet speeds are 110 fps to 150 fps faster than the Winchester 71 gr. FMJ ammo on the American market. Not only is our bullet heavier than any other American made 32 ACP ammo, but it is moving about 15% to 20% faster - with that heavier bullet! title: For Sale:  Arisaka Type 99 7.7 Full MUM, Full AA Sites, All #s Match Bayonet Avail. LOW $$
postcontent: NOT a last ditch model! Not Sporterized in any way! I went over all 6 pages of Arisakas listed on the biggest gun website as well as ARMSLIST and I can honestly tell you that there is NO other NON-Last ditch (cruder finish, fixed rear site, no chromed bore and more..) Type 99 with a Mum that is close to this price. There are a couple that seem close, but take a closer look and you will see missing rear site parts, cleaning rod and a buttplate on one ($75 to replace), altered stocks on several and though this one is no beautiful deep blue, it is not corroded like others here. Some are missing the top piece of wood too. Narrow down those that are complete, then that are all numbers matching and then have a MUM. You are down to a few listings on ALL of the gun websites, and this is a LOT less $$. Be careful for sporterized guns with cut stocks as they lose almost all collector value. Make sure you are not looking at a Last Ditch model as well, as they are a different gun than this one.  I am beginning this listing before the replacement (original parts) screws arrive from Numrich. A few of the screws had buggered slots and I am replacing any that are not nice.(the photo of the front end shows this, as those and the rear band screw are coming) Tested to be the strongest action after WW2 and continues to be the basis for custom guns of any caliber, this is the rifle that was the basis of the Japanese army in their quest for 1/2 the world. This one may not be the finest bluing as the color has faded a lot at the barrel end (the receiver is nice) but it is super clean steel with no corrosion. Some have that rough and mottled surface but this one is fine except for the faded front end. The receiver is much better with 50-60% original dark finish in front to 80% towards the rear. This is NOT from hard use either, as the inside parts show very little use. The bottom metal pieces are a more even mottled gray which seems to be the average on these. (I considered replacing the bottom magazine cover and trigger guard as it is only $30 to get a nicer finished one and these are not numbered parts)This rifle is the only one of the 9 I have had that has matching numbers on the bolt as well as any parts that have numbers. The firing pin matches, the bayonet lug in front matches, the safety matches...it is a full numbers matching gun. About the firing pin and bolt, they appear close to new. There is little to no wear on the sear surface from firing and the original deep black color that is on the pin and alot of the bolt rubs off quickly to shiny metal from use. (I have had 9 of these) The firing pin is nicer than a brand new replacement one I had ordered for another and this one has the matching serial number. The bore is clean as all were chrome lined, and the bullet test passes. (I will provide a photo of a .311 bullet stuck in the bore)The MUM has not been defaced or even lined out or rubbed. These are a lot harder to find, and I can not find any import marks either. All Type 99s turned in to US forces should have MUMs removed so this may be a vet bring back. Looking at all Type 99s for sale on all sites, a little less than 5% have the MUM which was the symbol of the emperor's property. One of the best features is the rear site, as it is the Anti-Aircraft design and all original parts are there (another hard to find quality) including both arms. They made these to allow for lead when firing at low flying planes. I have seen some people use these on shotguns for skeet! The wood is in good shape for Type 99s, as I have very rarely seen one with super wood, and those went for over $800 on Gunbroker. The ones that sold for over $800 were just like this one, but they had beautiful dark metal and wood. This will not be even close to half of that price. Oh, the original cleaning rod is present and the locking button works too. That saves you $35 to have one shipped from Ebay. The rifle is not complete without the rod as it changes the profile. The ONLY original option that is not present is the folding monopod, and I have only seen 3 or 4 that had that (the $800 ones). They make a perfect modern one for $30 if you want to make this complete and it is also not a numbered part. The rear band has the mounting part already. I also have an original bayonet that has a blade that was never sharpened and when I got it, it was layered in yellow dried grease which I was told was the original preservative. The blade has been in and out of the metal scabbard which is also very nice condition. I have no idea if the bayonet was polished or rubbed as some are blued but some are also silver like this. The bayonet is NOT included with the rifle but will be available for a discounted price if purchased with the rifle. The number on the bayonet is not matching. The bayonet will be $75 additional and if you look up these bayonets, the only ones around that price range are pretty beat up, if there are ones at that price.  I listed photos of the wood and scabbard as this is a very fine condition bayonet with the hooked quillon. The metal on the bottom of the rifle is all patina and a darker gray as the blue has changed over the decades as is the buttplate. The buttplate and bottom pieces are not satin smooth either but no corrosion. Just long term storage and these were not made for long term anything. These were a wartime product but even so, they took great care in making them super reliable and super strong. Only at the end of the war when defeat was around the corner, did they make the "LAst Ditch" versions with greatly simplified design and much cruder and rougher finishing.  75 years have passed since this was made in wartime. I am listing this Type 99 at $325 and I will also be looking up the armory and date of production which I will have when the screws arrive. I am only posting basic photos until I have the parts and it is all put together. Shipping is $35 to your FFL and C+R is fine. The bayonet, if bought with the rifle ships with it, saving another $12 or so. Your FFL must accept items from individuals and I will send all necessary ID. If you are local to the state of Florida, we can make other arrangements which MAY save a little for you. Paypal is fine but it MUST be discrete (no guns mentioned) and unless sent in a way that avoids fees, it will have an additional $10 which is only a PART of their fees. You are getting a great collector and shooter here. All numbers and the MUM and rear sites are awesome to find on the same gun, and if you look at what is offered for $100 more than this, this is a great deal. With the bayonet it is $400 for a complete package. MESSAGE ME for another 8 photos and I will have the new screws and complete rifle photos within the week
